younger dialysis patients treated simultaneously.
METHODS: In the last 5 years, all cases beginning dialysis in our institution 
who were above 75 years of age were reviewed, as well as cases aged between 50 
and 60 years who started dialysis during the same period. Between January 1996 
and December 2000, among a total of 429 new chronic dialysis patients, 67 ESRD 
patients over 75 years (15.6%) and 66 patients between 50 and 60 years (15.4%) 
